# FUNCTION: PRN
#
# 7 parameters must be previously defined:
# NSTEP:        Number of STEP
# PRN_NAME   :  Printer Identification
# PRN_I      :  Data File to print
# PRN_FMT    :  Format File
#
# PRN_TYPE: List of values - STARJET, STARPDF, WORD, DAESEND
# PRN_OUT:  indicates if WEB AND/OR PRINT output
#
# Subject:  Generic Function for Printing
# The report is printed either on the unix printer or to a netware printer
# depending information defined 
#
# The report is directly printed to Unix printer if the geographic and 
# production site are the same and the unix printer is defined
# Otherwise, the report file and its associated control file are sent to 
# the printing pool. They are two control files. The ftp file contains 
# information to connect the remote printing server. The dae file is used as
# a command file by the VB daemon that will execute starpage on the printing
# server.
#
# HISTORICAL: HG 2001/02/22 - PRN_OUT variable added
# 
# 
